      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A systematic approach for memory leaks in embedded C++ involves tracking allocations and deallocations with a specialized tool. Consider using a memory debugging library or implementing custom heap wrappers that intercept `new` and `delete` calls to log every allocation site and size. You can then monitor these logs over the 4-6 hours of operation, looking for patterns where allocations occur without corresponding deallocations. This targeted logging will pinpoint the exact function or object responsible for the continuous memory growth.",
